A '''collegium''' is a [[France|French]] form of schooling that is both a [[secondary school]] and a [[college]].

==Information==
They are uncommon today. Most collegiums in the United States were built by [[Roman Catholic]] [[religious institute]]s. One example is the [[College of the Immaculate Conception (New Orleans)|College of the Immaculate Conception]] in [[New Orleans]], established by the [[Society of Jesus]] (Jesuits) in 1847.{{citation needed|date=January 2013}}

