'''Discipline-based education research''' ('''DBER''') is an [[interdisciplinary]] [[academic research|research]] enterprise that "investigates [[learning]] and [[teaching]] in a [[academic discipline|discipline]] [normally from the [[STEM fields]]] from a perspective that reflects the discipline's priorities, worldview, knowledge, and practices."<ref>[[National Research Council (United States)|National Research Council]]. Discipline-Based Education Research: Understanding and Improving Learning in Undergraduate Science and Engineering. Washington, DC: The National Academies Press, 2012. Available at [http://www.nap.edu/catalog.php?record_id=13362]</ref>
